  "local_port": 53180,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "If you're seeing a notification or message about a \"dock connected\" on your Android device when there isn't an actual dock connected, it might be due to an issue with the software or the hardware. Here are a few steps you can take to troubleshoot and potentially resolve this issue:\n\n1. **Restart Your Device**: Sometimes a simple restart can resolve temporary glitches. Switch off your device, wait for a few seconds, and then turn it back on.\n\n2. **Check for Connected Devices**: Ensure there are no external devices or accessories connected that might be misinterpreted as a dock.\n\n3. **Inspect USB Port**: Dust or debris in the USB port might cause false connections. Carefully inspect the port and clean it if needed using a can of compressed air or a gentle brush. Be cautious not to damage the port.\n\n4. **Safe Mode**: Boot your device into safe mode to check if any third-party app is causing the issue. In safe mode, only pre-installed apps will run. If the message doesn't appear in safe mode, a recently installed app might be the cause.\n\n   - To enter safe mode: \n     - Press and hold the power button until the power menu appears.\n     - Tap and hold \"Power Off\" until the safe mode prompt appears, then tap \"OK.\"\n   - To exit safe mode, simply restart your device.\n\n5. **Check for Software Updates**: Make sure your Android OS is up to date as updates can fix bugs that might be causing the issue.\n\n6. **Reset App Preferences**: Go to Settings > Apps, tap the menu (three dots) in the upper-right corner, and select \"Reset app preferences.\" This won't delete app data but will reset default apps and permissions.\n\n7. **Check Developer Options**: If developer options are enabled, make sure no specific settings related to USB configurations are altered.\n\n8. **Factory Reset**: As a last resort, consider a factory reset. This will erase all data on your phone and restore its original settings, so back up your important data first. You can perform a factory reset from Settings > System > Reset > Factory data reset.\n\n9. **Hardware Issue**: If none of the above solutions work, there might be a hardware issue with the USB connector or related components. In this case, contacting the manufacturer's support or visiting a professional repair service is advisable.\n\nTry these steps, and hopefully, the \"dock connected\" notification will stop appearing. If the problem persists, it may be necessary to seek professional repair assistance.",
